      "title": "JoyAI Image Edit — local model setup",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Required models (place under ComfyUI/models/)\n\n**diffusion_models/**\n- `joyai_image_edit_bf16.safetensors`\n\n**text_encoders/**\n- `qwen_3vl_8b_joyimage_bf16.safetensors`  (Qwen3-VL 8B, JoyImage fine-tune)\n\n**vae/**\n- `wan_2.1_vae.safetensors`  (AutoencoderKLWan; reusable with Wan2.1/Hunyuan-Video stacks)\n\nLocal staging: `/pfs/huangfeice/checkpoints/jdopensource/JoyAI-Image-Edit-ComfyUI-Staged/split_files/`\n\n## Edit-model wiring contract\n\n**Both the positive AND negative `TextEncodeJoyImageEdit` must receive `image` and `vae`.** Diffusers' pipeline builds `latent_model_input = cat([image_latents, noise_latents])` once and feeds it to both `noise_pred` and `noise_pred_uncond`. ComfyUI's CFG path runs `extra_conds` independently per conditioning, so the ref must be wired into both. Empty negative prompts still need `image`+`vae`.\n\n## Spatial alignment contract (architectural, not a workflow choice)\n\nJoyImage stacks reference latents along a new n-slot dimension and rotates `[ref, noise] -> [noise, ref]` at the model boundary. This requires `noise.spatial == ref.spatial` exactly — unlike QwenImage (seq-dim cat, tolerates different spatial).\n\nThe node enforces this by:\n1. snapping the input image to the nearest 1024-base bucket internally (matches diffusers `image_processor.py` BUCKETS),\n2. emitting the bucketed image as a second output,\n3. feeding that bucketed image into `VAEEncode` (for noise) **and** into the negative `TextEncodeJoyImageEdit` (for the negative ref).\n\nThis is why there is **no `ImageScaleToTotalPixels`** in front of the encoder path: bucketing happens inside the node, so both the noise latent and both reference latents land on the same H/W.\n\n## Sampler defaults (matches diffusers reference)\n\n| | value |\n|---|---|\n| steps | 40 |\n| cfg   | 4.0 |\n| sampler | euler |\n| scheduler | simple |\n\n**Flow shift (1.5) and the t-scale come from the model config**, not a node. JoyImage's `BASE` config in `supported_models.py` carries `sampling_settings = {\"multiplier\": 1000, \"shift\": 1.5}` and `model_base.JoyImage` runs under `ModelType.FLOW` (`ModelSamplingDiscreteFlow`). Do **not** insert a `ModelSamplingAuraFlow`/`ModelSamplingFlux` node — it would force `multiplier=1.0`, collapsing the trained t∈[0,1000] range back to t∈[0,1] and producing pure noise. Wire `UNETLoader` straight into `KSampler`, exactly as Qwen Image Edit ships.\n\n**Do not add `CFGNorm`** — JoyImage builds guidance-rescale into `_apply_model` directly; stacking another `sampler_cfg_function` raises by design.\n\nThe `CLIPLoader` `type` field is cosmetic for this checkpoint — state-dict sniffing routes Qwen3-VL JoyImage TE regardless of the dropdown value. Pick `joyimage` for clarity."
      ],
      "color": "#222",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
